## Chunk 3 — OCR pipeline

**Goal:** Given a `PIX*`, produce a sorted list of
`WordBox{text, x, y, w, h, confidence}` on a worker thread, without
blocking the UI.

### In scope
- `OcrEngine` class owning a `tesseract::TessBaseAPI*` initialised
  once at daemon startup with the `eng` model.
- `OcrEngine::recognizeAsync(PixPtr) -> QFuture<std::vector<WordBox>>`,
  running on a dedicated `QThreadPool`.
- Word extraction via `ResultIterator` at `RIL_WORD` level, capturing
  bounding box and confidence.
- Secure wipe: `explicit_bzero(pixGetData(pix), size)` before
  `pixDestroy`.
- `WordBox` lives in `src/search/BoundingBox.h`.

### Definition of done
- Golden-image fixture finds ≥ 95% of expected words at confidence > 60.
- Integration test asserts the main thread event loop runs while OCR
  is in flight.
- p50/p95 latency reported in CI output.

### Effort
~4 dev-days.

